HEADWORD: Orismology
<hw>O`ris*mol"o*gy</hw> <pr>(⟦omac⟧`r⟦icr⟧s*m⟦ocr⟧l"⟦osl⟧*j⟦ycr⟧)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <grk>"orismo`s</grk> a marking out by
boundaries, the definition of a word + <ets>-logy</ets>. See
<er>Horizon</er>.]</ety> <def>That department of natural history which
treats of technical terms; the science of defining technical
terms.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

